    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - REASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301656">Figure 56</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301656" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301656" filename="../figg13/G1301656.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Countershaft Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301657">Figure 57</hotlnk>
                shows the hub direction of the gears. First-reverse gear is an integral part of the countershaft, while
                the remaining gears are secured with individual woodruff keys under each gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301657" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301657" filename="../figg13/G1301657.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Hub Direction of Gears</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If you place a straight edge between these painted teeth, every gear on the countershaft
                will be in line (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301658">Figure 58</hotlnk>). When you set the countershafts in time, these marks will
                be directly across from each other.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301658" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301658" filename="../figg13/G1301658.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Gears on Countershaft in Line</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
